==English==
===Adjective===
'''involute'''
# [[difficult]] to [[understand]], or [[complicated]]
#{{botany}} (''of a leaf or petal'') having the [[edge]]s rolled inwards
#{{biology}} {''of some shells'') having a [[complex]] pattern of [[coil]]s
===Intransitive verb===
'''to involute'''
# to [[roll]] or [[curl]] [[inwards]]
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''involute'''
#{{mathematics}} a [[curve]] that cuts all [[tangent]]s of another curve at [[right angle]]s; [[traced]] by a point on a [[string]] that [[unwind]]s from a curved object
